<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="418" pageId="1" pageNumber="415" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1625,2012]" box="[199,978,1769,1796]" pageId="1" pageNumber="415">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1769,1795]" pageId="1" pageNumber="415">Description</emphasis>
. Female. Body length 
<quantity box="[593,682,1770,1796]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.3" pageId="1" pageNumber="415" unit="mm" value="4.3">4.3 mm</quantity>
; fore wing length 
<quantity box="[885,974,1770,1796]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" pageId="1" pageNumber="415" unit="mm" value="3.2">3.2 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1625,2012]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,151,321]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="416" pageId="1" pageNumber="415">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,263,1806,1832]" pageId="1" pageNumber="415">Head</emphasis>
. Head width 1.2 × its height in anterior view (
<figureCitation box="[788,876,1806,1832]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetId="figure-116@2.[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Gnathochorisis jasoni sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; E) mesosoma, dorsal view; F) propodeum, dorsal view." pageId="1" pageNumber="415">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). Face width at level of antennal sockets 1.8 × its height, 0.5 × head width, subpolished and closely punctate, transversely striate medially in lower part, sparsely setose (
<figureCitation box="[236,324,1878,1904]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetId="figure-116@2.[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Gnathochorisis jasoni sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; E) mesosoma, dorsal view; F) propodeum, dorsal view." pageId="1" pageNumber="415">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). Frons, vertex and occiput polished, sparsely setose (
<figureCitation box="[936,1024,1878,1904]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetId="figure-116@2.[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Gnathochorisis jasoni sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; E) mesosoma, dorsal view; F) propodeum, dorsal view." pageId="1" pageNumber="415">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
). Occiput somewhat depressed (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetId="figure-116@2.[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Gnathochorisis jasoni sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; E) mesosoma, dorsal view; F) propodeum, dorsal view." pageId="1" pageNumber="415">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
). Occipital carina present (
<figureCitation box="[490,577,1914,1940]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetId="figure-116@2.[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Gnathochorisis jasoni sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; E) mesosoma, dorsal view; F) propodeum, dorsal view." pageId="1" pageNumber="415">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
). Eyes large, convex, without setae, inner orbits subparallel, slightly diverge downward (
<figureCitation box="[285,372,1950,1976]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetId="figure-116@2.[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Gnathochorisis jasoni sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; E) mesosoma, dorsal view; F) propodeum, dorsal view." pageId="1" pageNumber="415">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). Clypeus width 2.0 × its height, weakly separated from face, posterior margin of clypeus very weakly convex (
<figureCitation box="[334,420,1986,2012]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetId="figure-116@2.[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Gnathochorisis jasoni sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; E) mesosoma, dorsal view; F) propodeum, dorsal view." pageId="1" pageNumber="415">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). Anterior tentorial pits distinct (
<figureCitation box="[785,872,1986,2012]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetId="figure-116@2.[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Gnathochorisis jasoni sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; E) mesosoma, dorsal view; F) propodeum, dorsal view." pageId="1" pageNumber="415">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). Malar space 1.6 × as long as basal width of mandible (
<figureCitation box="[223,309,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetId="figure-116@2.[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Gnathochorisis jasoni sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; E) mesosoma, dorsal view; F) propodeum, dorsal view." pageId="2" pageNumber="416">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). Subocular sulcus distinct, sharp and straight (
<figureCitation box="[840,926,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetId="figure-116@2.[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Gnathochorisis jasoni sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; E) mesosoma, dorsal view; F) propodeum, dorsal view." pageId="2" pageNumber="416">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). Mandible bidentate, strongly tapered, lower tooth small. Antenna shorter than body, with 21 slender flagellomeres, all flagellomeres longer than wide (
<figureCitation box="[1334,1423,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetId="figure-116@2.[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Gnathochorisis jasoni sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; E) mesosoma, dorsal view; F) propodeum, dorsal view." pageId="2" pageNumber="416">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
). Scape about twice as long as wide. First flagellomere 4.3 × as long as wide apically, second flagellomere 3.5 × as long as wide apically. Ocelli of moderate size, ocular-ocellar line as long as and postocellar line 1.2 × as long as maximum diameter of lateral ocellus (
<figureCitation box="[450,535,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetId="figure-116@2.[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Gnathochorisis jasoni sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; E) mesosoma, dorsal view; F) propodeum, dorsal view." pageId="2" pageNumber="416">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
). Temple moderately short, 0.4 × as long as the width of compound eye (
<figureCitation box="[1333,1418,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetId="figure-116@2.[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Gnathochorisis jasoni sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; E) mesosoma, dorsal view; F) propodeum, dorsal view." pageId="2" pageNumber="416">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
