</caption>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1940,2039]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1437,151,465]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="417" pageId="2" pageNumber="416">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,325,1940,1966]" pageId="2" pageNumber="416">Mesosoma</emphasis>
. Mesosoma 1.3 × as long as maximum height, polished. Epomia strong, well developed (
<figureCitation box="[1333,1422,1940,1966]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetId="figure-116@2.[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Gnathochorisis jasoni sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; E) mesosoma, dorsal view; F) propodeum, dorsal view." pageId="2" pageNumber="416">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
). Mesoscutum (moderately) subpolished with dense light setae (
<figureCitation box="[875,963,1976,2002]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetId="figure-116@2.[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Gnathochorisis jasoni sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; E) mesosoma, dorsal view; F) propodeum, dorsal view." pageId="2" pageNumber="416">Fig. 1E</figureCitation>
). Notauli coarsely and irregularly pitted, posteriorly widened, meeting in the center of mesoscutum (
<figureCitation box="[818,904,2012,2038]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetId="figure-116@2.[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Gnathochorisis jasoni sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; E) mesosoma, dorsal view; F) propodeum, dorsal view." pageId="2" pageNumber="416">Fig. 1E</figureCitation>
). Scutellum not particularly high, smooth, with lateral carinae anteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[442,528,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetId="figure-116@2.[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Gnathochorisis jasoni sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; E) mesosoma, dorsal view; F) propodeum, dorsal view." pageId="3" pageNumber="417">Fig. 1E</figureCitation>
). Epicnemial carina complete, ending at upper corner of mesopleuron (
<figureCitation box="[1333,1423,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetId="figure-116@2.[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Gnathochorisis jasoni sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; E) mesosoma, dorsal view; F) propodeum, dorsal view." pageId="3" pageNumber="417">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
). Sternaulus short but distinct (
<figureCitation box="[478,566,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetId="figure-116@2.[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Gnathochorisis jasoni sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; E) mesosoma, dorsal view; F) propodeum, dorsal view." pageId="3" pageNumber="417">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
). Mesopleuron, metapleuron and propodeum polished, with sparse setae (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetId="figure-116@2.[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Gnathochorisis jasoni sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; E) mesosoma, dorsal view; F) propodeum, dorsal view." pageId="3" pageNumber="417">Figs 1D, F</figureCitation>
). Propodeal carination complete (
<figureCitation box="[594,679,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetId="figure-116@2.[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Gnathochorisis jasoni sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; E) mesosoma, dorsal view; F) propodeum, dorsal view." pageId="3" pageNumber="417">Fig. 1F</figureCitation>
). Area superomedia parallel-sided, 1.8 × as wide as long. Short sections of posterior transverse carina connecting with lateral longitudinal carinae form small rounded apophyses (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetId="figure-116@2.[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Gnathochorisis jasoni sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; E) mesosoma, dorsal view; F) propodeum, dorsal view." pageId="3" pageNumber="417">Fig. 1F</figureCitation>
). Propodeal spiracle large, round, joined by short carina with pleural carina. Fore wing without areolet (
<figureCitation box="[1336,1424,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1978,2002]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,489,1955]" captionTargetId="figure-178@3.[164,1423,489,1955]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Gnathochorisis jasoni sp. nov., holotype, female A) metasoma, lateral view; B) metasoma, dorsal view; C) wings." pageId="3" pageNumber="417">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
). Pterostigma 2.8 × as long as wide. Vein 2m-cu with two bullae (
<figureCitation box="[874,963,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1978,2002]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,489,1955]" captionTargetId="figure-178@3.[164,1423,489,1955]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Gnathochorisis jasoni sp. nov., holotype, female A) metasoma, lateral view; B) metasoma, dorsal view; C) wings." pageId="3" pageNumber="417">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
). Vein 1cu-a oblique, almost interstitial of vein M&amp;RS (
<figureCitation box="[300,387,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1978,2002]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,489,1955]" captionTargetId="figure-178@3.[164,1423,489,1955]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Gnathochorisis jasoni sp. nov., holotype, female A) metasoma, lateral view; B) metasoma, dorsal view; C) wings." pageId="3" pageNumber="417">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
). Hind wing with nervellus (CU+cu-a) intercepted in lower 0.3, second abscissa of CU present, short (
<figureCitation box="[222,311,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1978,2002]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,489,1955]" captionTargetId="figure-178@3.[164,1423,489,1955]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Gnathochorisis jasoni sp. nov., holotype, female A) metasoma, lateral view; B) metasoma, dorsal view; C) wings." pageId="3" pageNumber="417">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
). Hind coxa smooth (
<figureCitation box="[549,638,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetId="figure-116@2.[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Gnathochorisis jasoni sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; E) mesosoma, dorsal view; F) propodeum, dorsal view." pageId="3" pageNumber="417">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
). Hind femur 3.6 × as long as maximum width. Hind tibia 3.2 × as long as wide. Tibial spurs slender, claws long and thick, strongly bent.
</paragraph>
<caption pageId="3" pageNumber="417" startId="3.[151,250,1978,2002]" targetBox="[164,1423,489,1955]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1978,2038]" pageId="3" pageNumber="417">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1978,2002]" pageId="3" pageNumber="417">FIGURE 2</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Ranjith &amp; Humala &amp; Priyadarsanan, 2022" authorityName="Ranjith &amp; Humala &amp; Priyadarsanan" authorityYear="2022" box="[290,519,1978,2002]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Gnathochorisis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="417" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jasoni" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[290,519,1978,2002]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="417">Gnathochorisis jasoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[530,615,1978,2002]" pageId="3" pageNumber="417">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[530,615,1978,2002]" pageId="3" pageNumber="417" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, holotype, female A) metasoma, lateral view; B) metasoma, dorsal view; C) wings.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,150,825]" pageId="4" pageNumber="418">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,323,150,176]" pageId="4" pageNumber="418">Metasoma</emphasis>
. First metasomal segment 1.7 × as long as maximum width posteriorly, subpolished, postpetiole longitudinally striate with distinct dorsal carinae reaching posterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[994,1081,186,212]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1978,2002]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,489,1955]" captionTargetId="figure-178@3.[164,1423,489,1955]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Gnathochorisis jasoni sp. nov., holotype, female A) metasoma, lateral view; B) metasoma, dorsal view; C) wings." pageId="4" pageNumber="418">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
); dorso-lateral carina just above spiracle (
<figureCitation box="[253,342,222,248]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1978,2002]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,489,1955]" captionTargetId="figure-178@3.[164,1423,489,1955]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Gnathochorisis jasoni sp. nov., holotype, female A) metasoma, lateral view; B) metasoma, dorsal view; C) wings." pageId="4" pageNumber="418">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
). Sternite and tergite fused, glymma absent, spiracle situated at basal 0.5 length of T1, apex of first sternite at 0.5 of segment (
<figureCitation box="[451,542,258,284]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1978,2002]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,489,1955]" captionTargetId="figure-178@3.[164,1423,489,1955]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Gnathochorisis jasoni sp. nov., holotype, female A) metasoma, lateral view; B) metasoma, dorsal view; C) wings." pageId="4" pageNumber="418">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
). Second metasomal tergite 0.8 × as long as maximum width posteriorly, longitudinally striate, with small thyridium, smooth and polished in posterior 0.25 (
<figureCitation box="[1022,1109,294,320]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1978,2002]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,489,1955]" captionTargetId="figure-178@3.[164,1423,489,1955]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Gnathochorisis jasoni sp. nov., holotype, female A) metasoma, lateral view; B) metasoma, dorsal view; C) wings." pageId="4" pageNumber="418">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
). Remaining tergites smooth, sparsely setose (
<figureCitation box="[337,427,330,356]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1978,2002]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,489,1955]" captionTargetId="figure-178@3.[164,1423,489,1955]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Gnathochorisis jasoni sp. nov., holotype, female A) metasoma, lateral view; B) metasoma, dorsal view; C) wings." pageId="4" pageNumber="418">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
). Ovipositor upcurved with dorsal subapical notch (
<figureCitation box="[1022,1114,330,356]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1978,2002]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,489,1955]" captionTargetId="figure-178@3.[164,1423,489,1955]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Gnathochorisis jasoni sp. nov., holotype, female A) metasoma, lateral view; B) metasoma, dorsal view; C) wings." pageId="4" pageNumber="418">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
). Ovipositor sheath 1.3 × as long as first tergite and as long as hind tibia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,150,825]" pageId="4" pageNumber="418">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,283,402,428]" pageId="4" pageNumber="418">Colour</emphasis>
. Body black except antennae, clypeus, mandibles, maxillary and labial palps, tegula, legs except apex of hind tibiae, metasomal sternites and ovipositor, which are yellow; pterostigma, apex of hind tibiae, second metasomal tergite posteriorly, metasomal tergites 3–6, and ovipositor sheath brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,150,825]" box="[199,392,510,537]" pageId="4" pageNumber="418">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,260,510,536]" pageId="4" pageNumber="418">Male</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
